        <section>
            <h2>üíæ Local Storage Usage</h2>
            <p>The extension uses Chrome's local storage for essential functionality:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>User Preferences:</strong> Dark mode settings, auto-analyze toggle</li>
                <li><strong>Usage Count:</strong> Number of unique searches analyzed (for freemium model)</li>
                <li><strong>Premium Status:</strong> Whether you've upgraded to premium</li>
            </ul>
            <p>All this data remains exclusively on your device and is never transmitted anywhere.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>üåê Network Activity</h2>
            <p>Local Competitor Spyglass makes zero external network requests:</p>
            <ul>
